# MediPulse — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Identity
This is **MediPulse**, a smart hospital health management system built with Next.js 14 (App Router), Supabase, and Claude API. It serves two primary user roles: **Doctors** and **Patients**.

## Tech Stack (Non-Negotiable)
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- **Backend/DB**: Supabase (Postgres + Realtime + Auth)
- **AI Layer**: Anthropic Claude API (`claude-sonnet-4-20250514`)
- **Real-time Vitals**: Simulated WebSocket engine (mock device data)
- **State Management**: Zustand
- **Charts/Viz**: Recharts
- **Voice**: Web Speech API + Claude for SOAP note structuring
- **PWA**: next-pwa for mobile installability

## Code Style Rules
- Always use TypeScript with strict types — no `any`
- Use server components by default; only add `"use client"` when necessary
- All Supabase queries go in `/lib/supabase/` — never inline in components
- All Claude API calls go in `/lib/ai/` — never inline in components
- Use Zod for all form validation and API response parsing
- Folder structure follows feature-based organization (see `PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`)
- Every component must have a JSDoc comment explaining its purpose
- Use `cn()` utility from shadcn for all className merging

## Design System
- Primary palette: Deep navy (`#0A1628`) + Electric cyan (`#00D4FF`) + Soft white (`#F0F4FF`)
- Alert colors: Critical = `#FF4444`, Warning = `#FFB800`, Normal = `#00C853`
- Font: `DM Sans` for UI, `JetBrains Mono` for data/metrics
- All cards use glassmorphism: `bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-md border border-white/10`
- Minimum touch target: 44x44px (mobile-first)
- All animated transitions use Framer Motion

## Security Rules
- NEVER expose Supabase service role key on the client
- All patient data access must verify RLS policies in Supabase
- Doctor can only see patients assigned to them (enforced at DB level)
- Patients can only see their own records
- All AI-generated clinical content must show a disclaimer

## File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Hooks: `useCamelCase.ts`
- Utils/lib: `kebab-case.ts`
- API routes: `route.ts` inside App Router folders
